&lt;p&gt;I have installed this patch, however bug is not resolved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cassandra 0.7 beta1, Ubuntu 10.04&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12969980" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 9 Dec 2010 22:35:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reopened for backport to 0.6&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970007" author="lenn0x" created="Thu, 9 Dec 2010 23:26:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Brandon,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I verified this with 0.6 branch. Error occurs without patch. Applied with patch, no more errors. Thx!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970221" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 10 Dec 2010 16:33:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970241" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 10 Dec 2010 17:36:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12970265" author="hudson" created="Fri, 10 Dec 2010 18:48:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra-0.6 #22 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.6/22/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra-0.6/22/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    correct ordering of drain operations so CL.recover is no longer necessary.  Patch by jbellis and brandonwilliams, reviewed by jbellis for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1408&quot; title=&quot;nodetool drain attempts to delete a deleted file&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1408&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1408&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
